Introduction

Kim Jaehwan is a South Korean singer under WAKEONE. He is mostly known for placing 4th in the Produce 101 Season 2 finale, making him a part of the project boy group Wanna One until their disbandment.

Jaehwan became a semifinalist on Korea's Got Talent 2 in 2012.

In 2016, he was invited to appear on a new music program about amateurs facing off against professional singers called Vocal War: God's Voice. In the pilot episode, Jaehwan earned the chance to proceed to the next round with his rendition of Boohwal's "The Beautiful Truth". He eventually emerged as the winner of the first episode with his performance of "Autumn in Front of the Post Office, " originally by Yoon Do-hyun.

He made his solo debut on May 20, 2019, with his first mini-album Another.

On September 21, Wake One Entertainment announced the transfer of singer Kim Jaehwan's management duties from Swing Entertainment to Wake One.

On May 31st 2024 Wake One announced they have renewed their contract with Jaehwan as well as announced he will be enlisting in the military on July 1st, 2024.
